HB 4091
1 (e) For military support of civil authorities for other duties authorized by Congress or
2 federal law.
3 (3) Neither the Governor, the Adjutant General nor any officer or employee of state
4 government, as defined in ORS 174.111, may facilitate, assist or coordinate in the
5 mobilization of a service member or unit of the Oregon National Guard that is called into
6 active service if the active service is for law enforcement duties or immigration enforcement
7 duties. For purposes of this subsection, “immigration enforcement duties” does not include
8 support, logistics or surveillance duties that are part of a border security operation.
9 (4) The Governor may not give consent for, nor may the Adjutant General allow, a ser-
10 vice member or unit of the Oregon National Guard to be mobilized into active service if the
11 mobilization of the service member or unit into active service results in the Oregon National
12 Guard being effectively incapable of responding to a statewide emergency, such as a natural
13 disaster or act of terrorism.
14 (5) Nothing in this section prohibits the Adjutant General or any officer or employee of
15 state government from carrying out federal or state laws relating to the rights and privileges
16 of service members of the Oregon National Guard.
17 SECTION 3. The militia or armed forces of another state, territory or district of the
18 United States may not enter the borders of this state for the purpose of performing military
19 duty within the borders of this state or perform military duty within the borders of this
20 state, unless:
21 (1) The Governor permits or authorizes the militia or armed forces to enter the borders
22 of this state or perform military duty within the borders of this state; or
23 (2) The militia or armed forces are serving in a federal active duty status under the au-
24 thority of the President of the United States.
25 SECTION 4. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
26 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
27 on its passage.
